{
  "texts": [
    "The values 0.5 and 0.2 were the most commonly reported dropout rates across the different networks.",
    "L2 Regularization, sometimes called weight decay, adds a penalty to the loss function based on the magnitude of the neurons' weights.",
    "This penalty discourages the learning process from assigning too much importance to any single neuron.",
    "Loss Function evaluates how well the network was able to model the training data.",
    "Binary cross-entropy was by far the most common loss function and is used for binary classification problems."
  ]
}